OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1777983071
OL,3,CTwo cabin crew members arrested after
OL,4,Cconcerns raised
OL,6,FBoth cabin crew staff were arrested
OL,7,Fafter initial breath tests showed
OL,8,Freadings were above the limit for
OL,9,Faviation duties.
OL,11,FHowever, further tests in custody
OL,12,Frevealed they were within the legal
OL,13,Flimit, and both individuals were
OL,14,Freleased without charge.
OL,16,FA spokesperson for Greater Manchester
OL,17,FPolice said: "Police attended the
OL,18,FManchester Airport on 2 May 2026 after
OL,19,Fconcerns about the fitness of two
OL,20,Fcabin crew members to perform their
OL,21,Fduties.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/3
